==English==

===Pronunciation===
*smĕl, /smɛl/, /<tt>smEl</tt>/

===Noun===
'''smell''' (''[[countable]] and [[uncountable]]; plural'' '''[[smells]]''')

#A [[sensation]], pleasant or unpleasant, detected by inhaling air (or, the case of water-breathing animals, water) carrying [[airborne]] [[molecule]]s of a substance.
#:''I love the smell of fresh bread.''
#(''physiology'') The [[sense]] that detects [[smell]]s.

====Synonyms====
*(''sensation''):
**(''pleasant''): [[aroma]], [[fragrance]], [[odor]]/[[odour]], [[scent]]
**(''unpleasant''): odor/odour, [[niff]] (''informal''), [[pong]] (''informal''), [[reek]], [[stench]], [[stink]], [[whiff]] (''informal'')
*(''sense''): [[olfaction]] (''in technical use''), [[sense of smell]]

